result.execSummary:
The defendant Brian T Costigan was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • OWI (3rd), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Fine is to be paid at $50 per month commencing 09-01-2015; alternate 35 days jail, consecutive.

Reimbursement for Blood Draw costs to be paid/forwarded to Waukesha Co Clerk of Courts for City of New Berlin Police Department.  Blood draw costs, DNA surcharge and search warrant fee are to be paid along with fine payment plan.

Huber with standard release conditions to commence FORTHWITH.
Court orders 84 days credit and if the defendant is revoked, no credit to be applied.

AS OF 11/04/15: Court amends that Defendant IS NOT ENTITLED to the 84 days credit.

01/18/2016 AFTER FURTHER REVIEW, COURT GRANTS DEFENDANT'S MOTION FOR 84 DAYS CREDIT.
Consecutive to: any other sentence.
Should have been Revoked, not suspended
Ignition Interlock to be installed on every vehicle OPERATED, TITLED OR REGISTERED to the defendant.
Attendance at a Victim Impact Panel meeting on 08-19-2015 or one of the following meetings or serve 20 days huber, consecutive.

Defendant Brian T Costigan in court, in custody, with attorney Jorge R Fragoso.   Timothy F. Westphal appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 1.  Court finds defendant guilty. Ct. 2 and Ct. 3 dismissed and read-in. 

Court orders the following: 
Ct. 1:
-  180 days jail with Huber consecutive to any other sentence to commence FORTHWITH.  Huber with standard release conditions. Court Orders 84 days credit and if the defendant is revoked then there will be no credit. 
-    33 months Drivers License Revocation. 
-    33 months Ignition Interlock every vehicle TITLED OR REGISTERED to defendant
- Attendance at the Victim Impact Panel meeting on August 19, 2015 or one of the next ones or 20 days Huber consecutive.
- Alcohol Assessment 
- Blood Test Reimbursement of $35.00 paid through Waukesha County Circuit Court to be forwarded to New Berlin Police Department - append to fine.
- Search Warrant Fee of $6.00 paid through Waukesha County Circuit Court to be forwarded to District Attorney's Office - append to fine.  
- Fine totaling: $1494.00 to be paid at rate of $50.00 per month commencing 09/01/2015; alternate 35 days jail - consecutive
- DNA Surcharge of $200.00 - append to fine.
Plea/sentencing hearing on July 8, 2015 at 09:30 am.

Defendant Brian T Costigan in court, in custody, with attorney Jorge R Fragoso.    District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Defense is requesting a plea/sentencing date in the beginning of July. Court grants request.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for July 8, 2015 at 09:30 am.
Hearing on June 9, 2015 at 10:00 am.
Hearing on May 20, 2015 at 09:00 am.

Defendant to comply with I.D. Processing.  Absolute sobriety, defendant is not to possess or consume any alcohol.  Defendant is not to use/possess any controlled substances without a valid prescription and take as prescribed.  Defendant is not to operate a motor vehicle unless properly licensed.  Defendant to report/comply with Wisconsin Community Services (WCS) Intoxicated Driver Program  Defendant to report within the first business day after posting bail or released from custody.

Defendant Brian T Costigan in court, in custody.   District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin.    Court advises of right to an attorney.    Defendant to apply at Public Defender's Office for representation.  NOT GUILTY PLEA ENTERED BY COURT.
